  <description><![CDATA[<p>Overlooking the rushing waters of the River Lech and surrounded by the majestic peaks of the Rüfikopf mountains. Hotel Arlberg's location is idyllic, and matched by its centrality. Directly opposite the Rüfikopf lift - your gateway to the mountains - you'll have adventure at your fingertips and the bustle of this pretty town nearby.</p>
<p>Each of the hotel's 51 rooms are individually designed for an exceedingly comfortable stay. Exquisite upholstery, Egyptian cotton bed linen and luxurious Le Labo bath products are among the little touches that make this place stand out.</p>
<h2>Five-star service and an impressive wine cellar</h2>
<p>Lavish breakfasts, local produce, classic Austrian dishes, and silver service are part of the delightful dining experience here. The impressive wine cellar has over 700 European vintages and is a wine connoisseur's paradise.</p>
<h2>Ultimate luxury in the award-winning spa</h2>
<p>The newly re-modeled award-winning Arlberg Spa claims to be one of the finest in <a data-udi="umb://document/f5a2404579b84c448ac2a43bfaacfdd0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f5a2404579b84c448ac2a43bfaacfdd0}" title="Lech">Lech</a>. Immerse yourself in a world of relaxation: Hydrotherapy showers, stylish saunas and steam facilities, and a myriad of relaxation rooms. The connected indoor and outdoor pools and the terrace offer spectacular mountain views. Swim some lengths, relax in the massage jets, or lounge on the poolside beds.</p>]]></description>
