  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Austrian Twins</strong> are around 25m² and sleep two to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). These rooms have a lounge area and an ensuite with shower.</p>
<p><strong>Comfort Austrian Twins</strong> are around 35m² and sleep two to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). These rooms have a lounge area and an ensuite with shower/bath, and are also available with a balcony (supplement applies).</p>
<p><strong>Junior Suites</strong> are around 55m² sleep two to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed). These rooms have a lounge area and an ensuite with bath and separate shower.</p>
<p><strong>Jagdhof Suites</strong> are spacious rooms at around 80m². They sleep two to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed) and have a separate bedroom, balcony, lounge area, and an ensuite with bath and separate shower</p>
<p><strong>Standard Singles</strong> are around 18m² and have an ensuite with bath or shower.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Singles</strong> are slightly larger, at around 22m². These rooms have an ensuite with bath or shower.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Minibar</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in: <strong>4pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out:<strong> 11am</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tourist tax of approx. €3.80 per person per night is payable locally (children under 14 years are exempt).</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
